    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Customer Preference on Idbi Fortis Life Insurance Products at Idbi Fortis</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Ravi sankar</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Customer Preference<br />Insurance Products</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P4819</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Unlike the physical assets, which decrease in value with passage of time, the individual becomes more experienced and more matured as he advances in age. This raises his earning capacity. The purpose of life insurance is to protect the income of individual and provide financial security to his family, which is dependent on his income in the event of his premature death. The individual himself also needs financial security for the old age or on his becoming permanently disabled when his income will stop. Insurance has an element of savings in certain plans. Insurance is primarily collective co-operation to share a particular risk.. To know about the opinion on Insurance has taken as market sources for the products and to analyzing the view of the doctors and pharmacists.
The primary aim of the study is to get a deep insight into the Customer Preference of IDBI Fortis life Insurance co limited in Chennai. With special emphasis towards market linked (ULIP) plans. The very necessity of taking up this case is that life insurance companies are slowly moving away from the traditional endowment plans and focusing more on market linked plans.
The study also focuses to understand the customerâ€™s opinion on services, advertisement and
flexibility in payment of premium
I have adopted DESCRIPTIVE RESEARCH for my study. This is used to establish accurate description of variables relevant to the decision being taken without demonstrating the existence of the relationship between variables. Descriptive research can be Cross Section or Focus Group.
The data has been analysed and interpreted with the help of statistical tools. Chi-square has been employed to present the accurate representation of the data
The education qualification of the respondent plays a vital role while investing in market link
plans. And also the advisors should be provided with good training about the products
before they meet the customers.
There is also difficulty for the respondents to monitor the market regularly which many of
the respondents are not willing to do. So the company should create awareness of markelink plans and winning the confidence of the customer</td></tr>
